{
  "schemaVersion": "1.0.0",
  "id": "cloudwatch-data-source-add",
  "title": "Add CloudWatch as a data source",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": "Grafana includes built-in support for Amazon CloudWatch, so there's no plugin to install. In this milestone, you add the CloudWatch data source to your Grafana Cloud instance.\n\nLet's walk through the steps together."
    },
    {
      "type": "section",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "multistep",
          "content": "In the navigation menu, navigate to **Connections > Data sources**.",
          "steps": [
            {
              "action": "highlight",
              "reftarget": "a[data-testid='data-testid Nav menu item'][href='/connections']",
              "requirements": ["exists-reftarget", "navmenu-open"]
            },
            {
              "action": "highlight",
              "reftarget": "a[href='/connections/datasources']",
              "requirements": ["exists-reftarget", "navmenu-open"]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "interactive",
          "action": "highlight",
          "reftarget": "[data-testid='data-testid data-source-add-button']",
          "requirements": ["exists-reftarget"],
          "content": "Click **Add new data source**."
        },
        {
          "type": "interactive",
          "action": "formfill",
          "reftarget": "input[placeholder='Filter by name or type']",
          "targetvalue": "CloudWatch",
          "requirements": ["exists-reftarget"],
          "content": "In the **Filter by name or type** field, enter `CloudWatch`."
        },
        {
          "type": "interactive",
          "action": "button",
          "reftarget": "CloudWatch",
          "requirements": ["exists-reftarget"],
          "content": "Click **CloudWatch**.\n\nGrafana creates the data source and opens its **Settings** tab, where you'll configure the connection."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": "In the next milestone, you'll choose an authentication method and set your default AWS region."
    }
  ]
}
